name: Caulk Backer Rod
meta_title: Caulk Backer Rod
small_image_label: Caulk Backer Rod
thumbnail_label: Caulk Backer Rod
short_description: DAP Caulk Backer Rod is closed-cell polyethylene foam that is used to fill large joints before caulking. It works with most caulks and sealants by saving expensive caulk and preventing joint failure by partially filling large joints before applying caulk or sealant. Backer rod can also improve the energy efficiency of a home by helping to insulate and prevent drafts. Use it indoors or outdoors on a variety of projects including windows and doors, wall joints, foundations and cracks in pavement.
summary:
• 12

  • 2.0 lb.

  • 18"x14"x10"
meta_keyword: Caulk Backer Rod

name: Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patch
meta_title: Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patch
small_image_label: Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patch
thumbnail_label: Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patch
short_description:
Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patches are a unique and innovative drywall repair solution that is perfect for completing permanent repairs on damaged walls and ceilings. No more waiting for spackling to dry or messy sanding. DAP Eclipse allows you to patch drywall damage and paint immediately, allowing you to finish your project faster. This all-in-one, mess free solution not only provides a permanent, long-lasting repair but also superior impact resistance for areas that may see reoccurring impact, such as behind a door.
  • 4X stronger than drywall itself - Superior impact resistance
  • All-in-one, mess free - No spackling, sanding or tools required
  • Finish project faster - Paint immediately & finish in minutes
  • Permanent, long-lasting - Won't peel or lose adhesion over time
meta_keyword: Eclipse™ Rapid Wall Repair Patch

name: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit
Group_Name: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit
meta_title: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit
small_image_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit
thumbnail_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit
short_description:
Low Density (1.0 pcf) Spray Foam is an open-cell, non-structural air sealing and insulating foam for use in both new construction and renovation of industrial, commercial, agricultural and residential properties.
  • Permanently air seals the building envelope
  • Reduces energy loss and use of fossil fuels
  • Class A fire rated
  • 1.0 PCF open-cell insulating foam
  • Wont shrink or settle like cellulose
  • Can be used to repair low density spf
  • Reduces sound transmission
  • Expands to fill smallest to largest gaps, cracks, and holes, reducing air exchanges
meta_keyword: Touch 'n Seal 1.0 PCF Spray Foam Kit

name: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF FR Standard
meta_title: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF FR Standard
small_image_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF FR Standard
thumbnail_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF FR Standard
short_description:
1.75 PCF FR Standard foam is a closed cell spray foam insulation that provides Class A fire retardancy as well as thermal insulating and sound attenuating properties. 1.75 PCF FR is suitable for use in commercial, residential, transportation and many other applications.
  • High r-value 6.2 at 1" (25mm)
  • Airseals and saves energy
  • Closed cell structure
  • Class A fire rated
  • Does not shrink or settle
  • Compatible with all fiber insulation systems including cellulose, fiberglass and stone wool
  • Significantly increases structural strength
  • Reduces sound transmission
meta_keyword: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF FR Standard

name: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF Slow Rise
meta_title: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF Slow Rise
small_image_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF Slow Rise
thumbnail_label: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF Slow Rise
short_description:
Slow Rise 120 is a two-component foam system, available in a variety of low-pressure dispensing units and is designed for pour-in-place applications where foam needs to completely fill cavities or spaces without creating voids or excessive pressure. Uses include insulating difficult to reach voids in construction projects and OEM insulation or cavity filling applications like transportation vehicles/trailers and marine flotation.
  • 121 second gel time for excellent flow-ability
  • 1.75 PCF closed cell rigid foam
  • Class A fire rated
  • Does not shrink or settle
  • Meets the US Coast Guard requirements for flotation material 33CFR 183.145
  • Increased flow time to completely fill gaps, corners, holes, and cavities
  • Not to be used for filling gypsum board stud wall cavities, as wall distortion or damage may occur
meta_keyword: Touch 'n Seal 1.75 PCF Slow Rise

meta_title: Touch 'n Seal 2.0 PCF FR Standard

thumbnail_label: Touch 'n Seal 2.0 PCF FR Standard

name: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
Group_Name: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
meta_title: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
small_image_label: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
thumbnail_label: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
short_description:
StormBond 2 is a two-component roof tile adhesive that attaches low, medium, and high profile clay and concrete roof tile to a wide range of approved underlayments. Storm Bond 2 meets Miami-Dade County requirements and is also approved under Florida Building Code.
  • Superior bonding strength
  • Two-component polyurethane foam adhesive
  • Miami-Dade and Florida Building Code approved
  • Fast cure time
  • Reduces tile breakage during installation
  • May be walked on within minutes
meta_keyword: Touch 'n Seal Storm Bond 2 Roof Tile Adhesive
